			<h3 ><a href="#p1019">Re: Collision Component / Trigger Component</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=1019&amp;sid=a3a20d64bd71fc50b16ad3e347cb0cc4#p1019"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=97&amp;sid=a3a20d64bd71fc50b16ad3e347cb0cc4" style="color: #000066;" class="username-coloured">thelinuxlich</a></strong> &raquo; 21 Jun 2011, 11:45 </p>

			

			<div class="content">Remember our chat weeks ago about this, what about an entity called &quot;Global&quot; which would have specific components to deal with Ploobs Engine? A common example of the ES dealing with Events is in the InputSystem, the difference is that the input doesn't have a list, but I can see the same pattern applied to a System exclusively iterating the list of messages and doing necessary logic on them, then removing it from the list.</div>

			

		</div>

		
