		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p1021">Re: Collision Component / Trigger Component</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=1021&amp;sid=a3a20d64bd71fc50b16ad3e347cb0cc4#p1021"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=97&amp;sid=a3a20d64bd71fc50b16ad3e347cb0cc4" style="color: #000066;" class="username-coloured">thelinuxlich</a></strong> &raquo; 21 Jun 2011, 12:10 </p>

			

			<div class="content">Let's see some examples of Systems dealing with Events:<br /><br />This is the source of a game called Tankz, it uses Artemis<br /><br />Here the system implements a CollisionListener interface to talk with the physics engine:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://gamadu.com/svn/tankz/trunk/src/com/tankz/systems/physics/PhysicsSystem.java">http://gamadu.com/svn/tankz/trunk/src/c ... ystem.java</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Here the system instantiates a NetworkListener to deal with chat messages:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://gamadu.com/svn/tankz/trunk/src/com/tankz/systems/network/ClientNetworkSystem.java">http://gamadu.com/svn/tankz/trunk/src/c ... ystem.java</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Here the system implements a KeyListener interface to talk with the game input:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://gamadu.com/svn/tankz/trunk/src/com/tankz/systems/player/PlayerTankMovementSystem.java">http://gamadu.com/svn/tankz/trunk/src/c ... ystem.java</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Here an example of a system talking with another system(Crosshair needs Camera, which implements MouseListener to get mouse input and draw the crosshair image):<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://gamadu.com/svn/tankz/trunk/src/com/tankz/systems/rendering/CrosshairRenderSystem.java">http://gamadu.com/svn/tankz/trunk/src/c ... ystem.java</a><!-- m --><br /><br />What can we learn here? The developer is not trying to generalize all problems, each system has its own way to deal with things related to its aspect/behavior, which simplifies thought process. If our needs are simple, we can just create a &quot;MessagingSystem&quot; which iterates over a list of messages, do the logic and remove the message from the list; if it is complex, better treat each case exclusively(listeners, system-to-system communication).</div>

			

		</div>

		
